description: The Lexington Co. AB engages in the design, manufacture, and trade of textile and textile products. The company is headquartered in Stockholm, Stockholm. The company went IPO on 2015-02-18. Its offering comprises two main product areas: Home, further divided in such categories as Bed, including duvets, pillowcases, sheets, bedspreads, blankets and throws, Bath, including towels and bathrobes, Living, comprising kitchen towels, table runners, napkins, aprons, potholders and oven mitts, Details, including porcelain, glass and cutlery, and Home Accessories, comprising decorative objects, fragrance candles, frames and vases; and Clothing, comprising outerwear, t-shirts and pajamas. The Company’s products are available in more than 20 countries via a network of local resellers, agents, distributors, own stores, franchise shops and an online store. Lexington Company publ AB operates as a parent entity of a group comprising six subsidiaries.
name: The Lexington Company AB (publ)
